In the previous section, we dealt with an unsupervised learning problem in (5) and came up with a legitimate choice of the tuning parameter after re-parameterization of our reward function. As an alternative way to tackle this problem, we adopt clustering methods to select an appropriate subset of the immune response endpoints based on the observed values in different regimens. We assume that the correlation matrix \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
